In a message dated 8/14/01 10:51:22 PM Pacific Daylight Time, 
bsutton(-at-)gladstone.uoregon.edu writes:

> Hi all;
>  When I turn on the lights in my 6v bus, the gas needle goes all the way to 
>  full no matter how much gas is actually in the tank. When the lights are 
off,
>  
>  or on but with the dimmer all the way towards low light, the gage works 
> great. 
>  Interestingly enough, the same thing is happening in  both of my buses, so 
I 
> 
>  figured there was a big chance that someone else had experienced this and 
> knew 
>  what is happening.
>  

Bad ground- when you turn the lights on the guage grounds through the lights. 
 Loosen the guage holder to the bus thing, scrape it a bit move it around to 
renew the ground, and snug the knurls down.

